title.narrative: of VDCs in targeted districts with Gender-Based Violence Watch Groups established and functioning [PLC members integrated, Groups trained, Gvt budget allocated, monitoring system functioning, awareness-raising activities implemented, review meetings taking place]

actual.value: 2017:In 2017, 1153 gender-based violence watch group were newly established in 35 districts with 6,115 GBV WG members. In 2017, 908 awareness raising activities have been conducted by the GBV WG. Cumulative figure, in total is 805 VDCs in targeted districts have 5,660 GBV WGs which have been established

title.narrative: Number of boys, girls and women

actual.value: 2017:2,509 protection related cases were documented by women's group, including GBV WGs, in 35 districts. Cumulative figure, 23,202 cases, 17,712 women, 4,081 children and 1,409 men, were documented by PLC's and GBV WGs from Jan 2013 to Nov 2017
